‚óŹ Quick answer on consoleblank: no, it won't blind us. slub_debug=FZP catches
  corruption at the moment of the bad write, not at the eventual read ‚ÄĒ so even
  if we never crash again, the next bad write panics with a clean stack of the
  offending driver. consoleblank=0 just lowers the s2idle-entry rate so the soak
   test isn't all-or-nothing; pstore capture is unaffected. Dropping the
  lid-switch and idleAction changes from the plan.

